The film "Zakhar Berkut" at the box office has already collected 32 million UAH

05 Nov 2019, 19:25


Since the premiere on October 10, the Ukrainian historical film Zakhar Berkut has collected 32 million hryvnias in box office in Ukraine.

This was reported on the official film page on Facebook.
“More than 400 thousand spectators and over 32 million hryvnias. That’s just how much the historical action “Zakhar Berkut” has collected at the box office today, ”the statement said.
We will remind, earlier it was reported that the film "Zakhar Berkut" collected more than 13 million UAH in less than a week of rental.

Reference.

The film "Zakhar Berkut" is the largest Ukrainian film project since independence, filmed based on the novel by Ivan Franko of the same name. The director is Akhtem Seitablaev, one of the most famous contemporary figures of Ukrainian cinema and theater, the owner of many film awards, in particular, he worked on the films “Haytarma”, “Another's Prayer”, “Cyborgs”;
Starring - Robert Patrick, who was remembered by the audience in “Terminator 2”;
Star actors from around the world: Ukraine, USA, UK, Mongolia, Kazakhstan;
A huge international team of film professionals;
Filming in the incredible corners of the Carpathians;
Unique large-scale scenery, which has no analogues in domestic cinema;
Hundreds of unique handmade costumes, weapons, utensils and items;
Dizzying stunt tricks and special effects.

